#X text 326 128 This module combines the sine and square wave bass
signals.;
#X text 344 162 The signals are set up so that a flat-palm 'wobble'
will have a corresponding effect on the sound of the bass.;
#X text 326 207 The square bass is influenced by a single axis \, through
a vcf filter. Given the rich harmonics of this wave \, this was the
most responsive option.;
#X text 320 263 The sine wave \, on the other hand \, has its volume
influenced directly by that same axis. Its purpose is to 'fatten' the
square wave \, but given its lack of harmonics \, a vcf filter provided
less of a clear response than a direct control over its amplitude.
;
#X text 344 397 The total sound of the bass is broken into two parts:
an 'attack' and a sustained part.;
#X text 332 341 New bass notes (and elsewhere \, their corresponding
chords) are triggered by claps \, as detected by the 'clap detector'
module.;
#X text 326 442 Isolating the 'attack' part prevents the expanded accelerometer
signals from clashing with the onset of a new note.;
#X text 344 498 Before implenting this solution \, a 'pop' would sometimes
occur from the spike in the accelerometer values \, which would be
heard in the onset of the note. This new module eliminates that problem.
;
